[49m[38;5;10m+      1[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Code Review: Recipe 15.2 - Notification Timing Optimization
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      2[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      3[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Summary
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      4[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      5[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The Python companion is a well-structured, pedagogically sound implementation of the contextual bandit notification timing concepts from Recipe 15.2. The LinUCB algorithm is correctly implemented with proper matrix algebra. Safety constraints (quiet hours, frequency caps, deadline enforcement) are properly enforced as hard overrides on the model's recommendations. DynamoDB writes correctly use `Decimal`. The simulation demonstrates the learning loop clearly. Comments are excellent throughout, explaining "why" not just "what." Two warning-level issues exist: the `select_send_time` function duplicates the UCB computation logic from the agent class (breaking encapsulation and risking divergence), and the `apply_safety_constraints` fallback for frequency-capped patients returns a raw index 0 that doesn't account for the "defer to tomorrow" semantics described in the prose.
